1.title: Mothman
1.plot: In Point Pleasant, West Virginia, there lurks a winged man, with eyes that glow a fierce red, known as the Mothman. The sheer number of sightings has even awed the skeptics.

2.title: Champ
2.plot: In Lake Champlain, compelling evidence and eyewitness accounts tell the story of Champ, America's oldest monster.

3.title: The Bell Witch
3.plot: The small town of Adams, Tennessee is home to the Bell Witch, who cursed the Bell family with a poltergeist.

4.title: Tatzelwum
4.plot: The Tatzelwurm, legendary across all of Europe, is an ugly beast, possessing two powerful front claws but no hind legs and the body of a serpent.

5.title: Bigfoot
5.plot: Whether he's known as Bigfoot, Sasquatch, Yeti or the Abominable Snowman, the ape-like monster covered in fur has captivated imaginations the world over but northern California's Bigfoot Scenic Byway is the epicenter of Bigfoot sightings.

6.title: Ogopogo
6.plot: Over the past 150 years, sightings, photos and even videos of Ogopogo, a dark green snake of enormous length, has drawn tourists, zoologists and thrill seekers to the the shores of Okanagan Lake in British Columbia.

7.title: Bownessie
7.plot: A flurry of recent sightings of Bownessie, a strange, serpent-like creature, in England's Lake Windermere have prompted new investigations.

8.title: Storsie
8.plot: Northern Sweden is hiding a secret that for centuries was known only to locals: in the frozen waters of Lake Storsjo¨n, a strange creature lurks. Storsie is a lake monster described as having the body of a serpent and a cat-like head.

9.title: Normie
9.plot: In North Carolina's Lake Norman lies Normie, a lake monster reported to look like an overgrown alligator. Investigators theorize that Normie might be the result of a mutation caused by the nearby nuclear power plant.

10.title: Hodag
10.plot: The town of Rhinelander, Wisconsin is united by the local legend of a fierce creature with scales, horns and sharp claws known as a Hodag.

11.title: Lagarfljoy Worm
11.plot: Reports of a monstrous Iclandic lake worm known as the Lagarfjlot are investigated.

12.title: Pepie
12.plot: Minnesota's Lake Pepin is home to Pepie, a large, serpentine creature. An investigation is underway with a $50,000 reward offered for any conclusive evidence of Pepie's existence.

imdb.plot outline: BOOGEYMEN takes an in-depth look at the history of local monsters and travels to the small, picturesque towns where they appeared to listen to both believers and skeptics as they investigate the most recent sightings. The stories behind West Virginia's Mothman, Wisconsin's Hodag, Tennessee's Bell Witch and many other local monsters are explored.
